docs[1]{path,scope,note}:
  "https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/pull/396",project,"PR: cli-contracts decomposition"
body: "Decompose the `src/sdk/cli-contracts.ts` monolith (2631 lines, the lowest-rated\nCodeFactor file at grade B) into focused sibling modules under\n`src/sdk/cli-contracts/`, continuing the established barrel-split pattern\n(`commander-types`, `commander-mutation-options`, `enum-contracts`,\n`tool-option-contracts`, `tool-parameter-tables`).\n\n## What moved\n\n- `cli-contracts/string-lists.ts` (new leaf util) — `normalizeUniqueStringList`,\n  the unique/non-empty string-list helper shared by flag-alias dedup and MCP\n  schema key dedup (single source of truth).\n- `cli-contracts/flag-contracts.ts` — the `CliFlagContract`/`ToolOptionFlagContract`\n  interfaces, alias-metadata helpers, all ~70 `*_FLAG_CONTRACTS` arrays,\n  `resolveSubcommandFlagContractsForCommand`, and `toCompletionFlagString`.\n- `cli-contracts/tool-schema.ts` — `PmActionSchemaContract`, the per-action\n  parameter key sets, `PM_TOOL_ACTION_SCHEMA_CONTRACTS`, the strict + provider\n  schema builders, the schema version constants, and `_testOnlyCliContracts`.\n- `cli-contracts.ts` is now a thin re-export barrel (2631 -> 170 lines) so every\n  existing import site keeps importing from `./cli-contracts.js` unchanged.\n\n## Constraints honored\n\n- Zero behavior change: `pm contracts --full` snapshot (`tests/fixtures/contracts/full.json`)\n  is byte-identical; tool schema stays `4.0.4`.\n- Public SDK export surface unchanged (`toUniqueFlagContracts` stays internal,\n  re-imported by tool-schema only for the `_testOnlyCliContracts` test bundle).\n- 100/100/100/100 coverage preserved (5139 tests); ESLint + jscpd + static\n  quality gate green; tsc clean. No import cycle (the type-only barrel import in\n  `tool-option-contracts.ts` now points at the `flag-contracts.ts` sibling).\n- Upgraded 7 auto-generated boilerplate docstrings to behavior-describing prose\n  while relocating them.\n\nAdvances epic pm-92if (CodeFactor A -> A+): removes the worst-rated source file\nfrom the hotspot list and shrinks the per-file complexity surface CodeFactor grades."
